WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.760
An enzyme only works when it is folded into exactly the

2
00:00:02.860 --> 00:00:05.568
right shape. So what happens when the desert heats up?

3
00:00:06.366 --> 00:00:09.124
Folding is a tug of war between order and disorder.

4
00:00:09.224 --> 00:00:11.925
Add heat, and the disorder wins — the chain shakes

5
00:00:12.025 --> 00:00:14.390
loose and falls apart into a useless tangle.

6
00:00:15.266 --> 00:00:18.112
We track the folded fraction as temperature climbs.

7
00:00:18.212 --> 00:00:20.885
It holds steady while the protein is comfortable

8
00:00:20.985 --> 00:00:23.369
— then, past a melting point, it collapses.

9
00:00:25.266 --> 00:00:27.927
That tipping point is the melting temperature. Cross

10
00:00:28.027 --> 00:00:30.051
it, and half the enzyme is already gone.

11
00:00:30.133 --> 00:00:33.559
This single dial gates the whole toolkit: whatever fraction stays

12
00:00:33.659 --> 00:00:36.815
folded is the fraction of enzyme still doing chemistry. Lose

13
00:00:36.915 --> 00:00:39.202
it, and every downstream rate falls with it.

